HUNDRED and twenty-one South Africans who were in China and waiting to be repatriated back home, have safely landed at the Polokwane airport this morning.  Their flight landed around 10:30am.Â They are now being taken off the flight into the buses which will transporting the at the Ranch Hotel outside Polokwane where they will be quarantined for 21 days. The Ranch Hotel is situated about 37 Kilometers away from the Polokwane airport. Three buses have been allocated for their transportation.  Large number of soldiers and police have been deployed to the hotel to patrol the quarantine center. No one will be allowed to go into the hotel for the next 21 days until the quarantine period for the repatriated is over.